  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (f817db3 2022-08-16T00:03:50.309804091Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge create --keystore ./my-directory --password mypass\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nforge create only works with hardcoded file, as:\r\n```\r\nforge create --keystore ./my-directory/my-keystore-file  --password mypass\r\n```\r\nbut using as\r\n```\r\nforge create --keystore ./my-directory  --password mypass\r\n```\r\nwe get:\r\n```\r\nError:                                                                                                                                \r\nIO: Is a directory (os error 21)\r\n```",
